Options for viscos

viscos_options.Rd

Get the list of options for viscos. The available settings are listed in the details.

viscos_options(..., RESET = FALSE, READ.ONLY = NULL, LOCAL = FALSE)

Details

The provided options are listed below. In the following the standard setting for each option is given alongside a short explenation. Each one can be changed at will.

  • name_o = "qobs" ... Name of the \(o\)-column (observations).

  • name_s = "qsim" ... Name of the \(s\)-column (simulations).

  • name_lb = "lb" ... Optional lower bounds of the \(s\) data.

  • name_lb = "ub" ... Optional upper bounds of the \(s\) data.

  • name_COSyear = "yyyy" ... Name of the COSERO year-column.

  • name_COSmonth = "mm" ... Name of the COSERO month-column.

  • name_COSday = "dd" ... Name of the COSERO day-column.

  • name_COShour = "hh" ... Name of the COSERO hour-column.

  • name_COSmin = "min" ... Name of the COSERO minute-column.

  • name_COSposix = "posixdate" ... Name of the complete-date-column.

  • name_COSperiod = "period" ... Name of the marked-period-column.

  • name_COSperiod = "(m^3/s)" ... Unit-tag.

  • missing_data = -999 ... Additional marker for missing data.

  • color_o = "steelblue" ... Color associated with \(o\)-data.

  • color_o = "orange" ... Color associated with \(s\)-data.

  • of_limits = c(0,1) ... Limits for the objective functions visualization,

See also

Other viscos specifica: viscos_example

Examples

check "name_o":
viscos_options("name_o")

change and check "name_o":
viscos_options(name_o = "OtherData")
viscos_options("name_o")
